Not being able to digest and absorb most disaccharides and trisaccharides really is a shame. For example Lactulose (which is cleverly used as a laxative) is just fructose and galactose. To a low level peater it would sound insanely cool, but your body can't do anything with it...

Galkovsky's new lecture on Soviet theatre has an incredible bit about how when Lenin complained about the theatricalization of political life he was talking about how after 1917 meetings of the Soviets congress and the communist party were literally held in the Bolshoi theatre.

Lunacharsky also was a key figure behind the mummification of Lenin's cadaver and building his (Masonic in design) Mausoleum (which both would have been extremely against Lenin's personal wishes if he had the say), thus finally turning Lenin himself and his dead body into theatre

Lenin actually tried to close down the Bolshoi theatre multiple times because of this, but could do nothing about it, as it was under the control of Lunacharsky and Lunacharsky was one of the people who was absolutely untouchable in the USSR as he was a very high-ranking mason.
Fishing Boats in Winter, Etretat, Henri Matisse, 1921.
